---
const effectiveDate = "2025/09/04";
---

<main class="flex flex-col gap-10 font-primary">
  <div class="flex items-center font-primary flex-col">
    <h1 class="text-4xl">Terms of Service</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="flex items-start flex-col mx-60 font-primary gap-2">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Effective Date: {effectiveDate}</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      Welcome to Open Labs Nepal, an open-source platform developed by the
      Deerwalk Developers Community. By accessing or using this website, you
      agree to comply with and be bound by the following Terms of Service.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-start mx-60 text-2xl gap-2">
    <h2 class="">1. Purpose of the Platform</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      Open Labs Nepal is a community-driven platform where students across Nepal
      can share and access academic lab work. The platform aims to foster open
      collaboration, learning, and knowledge-sharing.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-start mx-60 text-2xl gap-2">
    <h2>2. Use of Content</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      All lab work published on this platform is submitted voluntarily by
      students and contributors. By accessing this content, you agree to use it
      solely for educational and non-commercial purposes. Plagiarism or
      unauthorized submission of someone else's work is strictly prohibited.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex items-start flex-col mx-60 font-primary gap-2">
    <h2 class="text-2xl">3. Contributing Lab Work</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      Contributions are made via public GitHub repositories. By submitting your
      work:
    </p>
    <ul class="text-xl list-disc">
      <li>
        You grant Open Labs Nepal the right to publish and display your
        contribution.
      </li>
      <li>
        You confirm that the work is your own or you have the right to share it.
      </li>
      <li>
        You understand that your submission will be publicly accessible and
        reusable by others under the terms of the open-source license applied to
        the repository.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-start mx-60 text-2xl gap-2">
    <h2>4. No Academic Endorsement</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      Open Labs Nepal is not endorsed by any university or college. Use of the
      platform does not substitute for official academic submissions or
      evaluations.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-start mx-60 text-2xl gap-2">
    <h2>5. Modification and Termination</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue access to any part
      of the platform at any time, with or without notice.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-start mx-60 text-2xl gap-2">
    <h2>6. Disclaimer</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      Open Labs Nepal provides all content "as is" without warranties of any
      kind. We are not liable for any loss or damages resulting from the use of
      this platform or its content.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-start mx-60 text-2xl gap-2">
    <h2>7. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      By accessing or using Open Labs Nepal in any manner, you acknowledge that
      you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms of
      Service. If you do not agree to these terms, you should discontinue use of
      the platform immediately.
    </p>
  </div>
</main>
